Package: waterml
Title: Fetch and Analyze Data from WaterML or CUAHSI WaterOneFlow Web Service
Version: 0.8
Authors@R: person("Jiri","Kadlec", email="jirikadlec2@gmail.com", role=c("aut", "cre"))
Description: The waterml package lets you connect to any CUAHSI WaterOneFlow
    web service from any hydroserver. To see list of available hydroservers,
    see http: //hiscentral.cuahsi.org. The package has four functions:
    GetServices(): show all public HydroServers from the HIS Central
    HydroCatalog. GetVariables(): Show a data.frame with all variables on the
    server. GetSites(): Show a data.frame with all sites on the server.
    GetValues(): Given a site code, variable code, start time and endtime,
    fetch a data.frame of all the data values. The data.frame has two columns:
    time and DataValue. This function has an optional "daily" parameter you can
    set daily="max", daily="min" or daily="mean" to get aggregated daily
    values.
Depends:
    R (>= 3.0.1)
Imports:
    XML
License: MIT + file LICENSE
LazyData: true
